## Selecting the input and output structure
This feature allows to select the input and output data schema to use to design the data transformation.

- Open the Mapper resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

- Select the input and output schemas from the **Input structures **and **Output structures **drop-down menus, respectively. For example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Important

By default, the Mapper uses the input data structure of the Reader resource to which it is connected in the pipeline.

If you modify the project's pipeline connecting the Mapper to a different Reader, the Mapper's input structure is not updated automatically, as this action would destroy any existing transformations and configurations defined by the user.

If the selected input or output data structure does not match the data structure of the connected Reader or Writer resource, respectively, in the Console you will find a warning message informing you that two connected resources are not communicating using the same data schema.

### Cloning a data structure
This feature allows to clone an existing data structure so that it can be modified without impacting the other Data Transformation resources that may be using it.

- Select a data structure and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Fork structure**). The system displays a warning message:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Click **YES, CONTINUE **to proceed.

- Enter the name of the new structure to create.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Click **CONFIRM**.

## Editing the input and output data structures
> Important

All changes applied to the data structure will also affect any Data Transformation resources using the same data structure.

If the selected input schema is the same schema used by the connected Reader resource, it will not be possible to edit it from the Mapper interface.

> Tip

If you need to modify a data structure that is currently in use by other resources, you can clone it so that it is disconnected from any other resource. For more information, see [Cloning a data structure](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-mapper-configuring-the-input-and-output-data-structure#cloning-a-data-structure) above.

- Move your mouse over the name of an element or attribute in the data structure. The  ![](data:image/png;base64,) icon is displayed; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click![](data:image/png;base64,) (**More**) to expand the context menu; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the required action:

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Repeat**

Create a logical clone of the selected element, i.e. a repetition that is only visible in the Mapper UI but not in the actual XML structure. This may be useful, for example, if you need to apply complex transformations to an element or repeat a transformation multiple times.

> Note

This action is only available for output schema elements.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Remove connect ions**

Remove all connections from the selected node.

> Warning

No confirmation is required. This action cannot be undone.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Show connect ions**

Show all existing connections for the current element in the mapping area, making them visible if hidden.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Delete**

Permanently delete the element or attribute from the structure.

> Warning

The system only displays a confirmation dialog when deleting elements with children. No confirmation is required for single elements or attributes.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

[**Details**](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-mapper-configuring-the-input-and-output-data-structure)

View and edit the configuration details of the selected element or attribute.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Add element**](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-mapper-configuring-the-input-and-output-data-structure#adding-an-element-to-the-structure)

Add an element at the same level as the selected element.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Add child element**](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-mapper-configuring-the-input-and-output-data-structure#adding-a-child-element-to-the-structure)

Add an element hierarchically nested under the selected element.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Add attribute**](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-mapper-configuring-the-input-and-output-data-structure#adding-an-attribute-to-the-structure)

Add an attribute to the selected element.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Duplicate**

Duplicate the element or attribute.

### Adding an element to the structure
This feature allows to add an element at the same level as an existing element in the ordered hierarchical structure.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

- Select![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add element**). A new element is added to the structure; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the new element, click![](data:image/png;base64,) and select![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) (**Details**) to open the Settings panel and configure the required parameters:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Name**

Name of the new element

**Dimension**

Maximum number of characters that the element can contain

**Min occurrences**

Minimum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

When set to **0**, the attribute is optional.

To set the parameter as optional, you may also select the **Optional **checkbox.

**Max occurrences**

Maximum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

If there is no limit to the number of occurrences, select the **Unbounded **checkbox.

### 
> Note

For more information, see [Editing an element or attribute](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-mapper-configuring-the-input-and-output-data-structure#editing-an-element-or-attribute) below.

### Adding a child element to the structure
This feature allows to add a child element under an existing element in the ordered hierarchical structure.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add child element**). A new element is added to the structure, hierarchically nested under the selected element; for example:

- Select the new child element, click ![](data:image/png;base64,) and select ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) (**Details**) to open the Settings panel and configure the required parameters:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Name**

Name of the new element

**Dimension**

Maximum number of characters that the element can contain

**Min occurrences**

Minimum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

When set to **0**, the attribute is optional.

To set the parameter as optional, you may also select the **Optional **checkbox.

**Max occurrences**

Maximum number of occurrences of the repetition

> Tip

If there is no limit to the number of occurrences, select the **Unbounded **checkbox.

### 

> Note

For more information, see [Editing an element or attribute](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-mapper-configuring-the-input-and-output-data-structure#editing-an-element-or-attribute) below.

### Adding an attribute to the structure
This feature allows to add an attribute to an element of the ordered hierarchical structure.

The functionality is useful, for example, when you want to define the properties or characteristics of an element of the structure.

- Select the required element from the panel on the left and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) to expand the context menu.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add attribute**). A new attribute is added to the structure, hierarchically nested under the selected element; for example:

- Select the new attribute, click ![](data:image/png;base64,) and select ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) (**Details**) to open the Settings panel and configure the required parameters:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Name**

Name of the new attribute

**Dimension**

Maximum number of characters that the attribute can contain

> Note

For more information, see [Editing an element or attribute](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-mapper-configuring-the-input-and-output-data-structure#editing-an-element-or-attribute) below.

### Editing an element or attribute
This feature allows to view and edit the configuration details of the selected element or attribute.

- Click on the name of an element or attribute to open its configuration panel on the right; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Edit the required fields, as described in the relevant sections above:

[Adding an element to the structure](/doxee-platform/docs/1-dt3-mapper-configuring-the-input-and-output-data-structure#adding-an-element-to-the-structure)

- [Adding an attribute to the structure](/doxee-platform/docs/1-dt3-mapper-configuring-the-input-and-output-data-structure#adding-an-attribute-to-the-structure)
